		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Each background palette line will take the form:<br />0=background<br />1=black outline<br />2=one color<br />3=another color</div>
<br />
<br />Does it mean that the background palette will be something like that ? :
<br />00=background color
<br />01=black outline
<br />02=one color
<br />03=another color
<br />04=background color
<br />05=black outline
<br />06=another color
<br />07=another color
<br />08=background color
<br />09=black outline
<br />0A=another color
<br />0B=another color
<br />0C=background color
<br />0D=black outline
<br />0E=another color
<br />0F=another color
<br />
<br />Or like that :
<br />00=background color
<br />01=black outline
<br />02=one color
<br />03=another color
<br />04=another color
<br />05=another color
<br />06=another color
<br />07=another color
<br />08=another color
<br />09=another color
<br />0A=another color
<br />0B=another color
<br />0C=another color
<br />0D=another color
<br />0E=another color
<br />0F=another color

		

		</td>
	</tr>
